  "script": "$500,000 from a detour? A Tennessee woman pulled off at an Ohio gas station on her way to a family reunion, grabbed a scratch-off on a whim, and walked out half a million dollars richer. One random stop. One impulse ticket. A 500,000 dollar payout. She wasn't even supposed to be there — the reunion was the plan; the jackpot was an accident. Most people scratch those tickets and win enough for another ticket. She scratched hers and won a house. Imagine explaining to your family why you're late: you stopped for gas and became rich. So would you have even bought the ticket?",
